Cell.Data: The number of TED XML files that contain the indicated data.
The data in this workbook was derived from analysis of 610.646 TED XML files.
The percentage of the Number column divided by the total number of files (601.646)
These files were "TED Export" files downloaded from TED Monitor Archive 2020 and 2021 from these URLs:
The name of the element at XPath /TED_EXPORT/FORM_SECTION/*, excluding NOTICE_UUID Where multiple such elements existed in one XML file, they all had the same name
The value of the "FORM" attribute in the Form element Where multiple Form elements existed in one XML file, they all had the same value for the "FORM" attribute
The number of different values of the "LG" attribute for the Form elements Where multiple Form elements existed in one XML file, they all had different values for the "LG" attribute
The value of the "VERSION" attribute of the "TED_EXPORT" element, or the value of the "VERSION" attribute of the Form element
The data was collated and analysed using Unix Bash, Perl and XQuery.

Where Form element was "MOVE" or started with "F", either the value of the "VALUE" attribute of the "LEGAL_BASIS" element, or "OTHER" where the element "LEGAL_BASIS_OTHER" existed. Where the "Schema" started with "R2.0.8", the value "32009L0081" Blank for all other cases
The value of the "TYPE" attribute of the "NOTICE" element

ss:Data.Font: The sheet "form-notice-legal-document", is designed to be used for a mapping of TED data and eForms Notice subtypes. That is, it should be possible using the information in this sheet to determine for any TED XML notice file, which eForms subtype it should be converted to.
It is in draft form, and more information is required, and then checked.
